events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 28 points, seven assists and seven rebounds, Bobby Portis added 23 points and 11 boards, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the New York Knicks 130-111 on Saturday, opening a two-game series with their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat the Knicks again in a one-sided series, with the teams set to meet again on Christmas

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 30 points, Jaylen Brown added 24 and the Boston Celtics kicked off their Christmas weekend in Southern California with a 145-108 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum, Jaylen Brown lead Celtics to a 145-108 rout of the Clippers

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored 22 points, Nikola Jokic had 18 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists and the Denver Nuggets held the Charlotte Hornets without a field goal for more than 11 minutes in the third quarter in a 102-95 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michael Porter scores 22 points, Nuggets use dominant 3rd quarter to beat Hornets 102-95

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 34 points and the Orlando Magic snapped a four-game skid with a 117-110 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 34 points, Magic beat Pacers 117-110 to snap 4-game losing streak

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Houston center Alperen Sengun figured out a way to make his matchup with New Orleans veteran Jonas Valanciunas look more like a mismatch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alperen Sengun has career-high 37 points, Rockets beat Pelicans 106-104

headlines.description: — On a scale of 1 to 10, Ja Morant was quick to give his rating of how his first three games with the Memphis Grizzlies have gone this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant scores 30 points in 125-119 win over Hawks as Grizzlies move to 3-0 since his return

headlines.description: — Pistons players sat in stunned silence, staring blankly ahead in their locker room after yet another loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons match NBA single-season record with 26th straight loss, fall 126-115 to the Nets

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 16 of his 30 points in the fourth quarter, Lauri Markkanen also had 30 and the Utah Jazz overcame a 17-point deficit to beat the Toronto Raptors 126-119 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Clarkson scores 16 of his 30 in 4th, Jazz overcome 17-point deficit to beat Raptors 126-119

headlines.description: — Max Strus had 26 points and seven assists to help the injury-depleted Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Chicago Bulls 109-95 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Max Strus scores 26 points to lead injury-depleted Cavaliers past Bulls, 109-95

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored a season-high 40 points and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 129-120 on Saturday night to snap a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores season-high 40 points, Lakers beat Thunder to end 4-game skid

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 39 points in a triple-double and the Dallas Mavericks routed San Antonio 144-119 on Saturday night after Spurs rookie star Victor Wembanyama was a late scratch when he sprained an ankle during warmups.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 39 points in triple-double, Mavs rout Spurs 144-119 as Wembanyama sits

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 28 points, Stephen Curry had 27 and the Golden State Warriors beat the Portland Trail Blazers 126-106 on Saturday for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson, Stephen Curry lead Warriors past Trail Blazers for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 34 points and 10 assists, Rudy Gobert added 21 points and 17 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the Sacramento Kings 110-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 34 points as the Timberwolves beat the Kings 110-98
